					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This records an endowment of one eighth (of a <hi rend="italic">vēli ?</hi>) of land to the west of the sacred tank, for burning a lamp in the temple of Tirukkuḍittiṭṭai-Perumāḷ at Amaṉi nārāyaṇa-chaturvēdimaṅgalam on the northern bank of the river, by Perumāṉ Pōṟṟi wife of a certain Neṟkuppai-uḍaiyāṉ. This is possibly an inscription of <hi rend="bold">Āditya II Karikāla</hi> son of Sundara-Chōḷa Parāntaka II. </p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
